# Session-start preflight verification

The `.cursor/hooks.json` `sessionStart` hook (script:
`.cursor/hooks/session-preflight.ps1`) fires once per session and kicks
off three background services so the operator never has to chase them
manually:

1. **Docker Desktop** — launched only if the daemon isn't already
   responding to `docker ps`.
2. **`tgv-sonarqube` container** — spawned via the
   `.cursor/hooks/start-sonar.ps1` helper, which polls `docker ps` for
   up to 2 min before running `npm run sonar:up`.
3. **Vite dev server** — `npm run dev` is started in a detached hidden
   PowerShell if port `5173` isn't already in the `Listen` state
   (covers both v4 and v6 loopback — Vite binds to `::1` by default on
   Windows).

The hook is **fire-and-forget**: it returns within ~1 s even when
Docker needs 30–60 s to boot. That means services may still be
warming up when you start working. Verify health before doing
sonar/preview-dependent work and recover anything that's missing.

## Verification (when relevant)

When a task actually needs one of the three services, run the
matching check first. Don't burn time on `docker ps` for
planning-only / pure-domain-test turns.

```powershell
# Docker daemon (gate for sonar)
docker ps                                                    # exit 0 = ready

# tgv-sonarqube container (only meaningful once Docker is up)
docker ps --filter "name=tgv-sonarqube" --format "{{.Names}}" # lists name if up

# Vite dev server (covers v4 + v6 listeners)
Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 5173 -State Listen -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
```

## Recovering gaps

- **Docker daemon down** → `Start-Process 'C:\Program Files\Docker\Docker\Docker Desktop.exe'`, then wait ~30–60 s.
- **Sonar container down** → `npm run sonar:up` (idempotent; safe to
  rerun even when partially up).
- **Dev server down** → `Start-Process powershell -ArgumentList '-NoProfile','-WindowStyle','Hidden','-Command',"Set-Location '<repo>'; npm run dev" -WindowStyle Hidden`.

If Docker Desktop isn't installed at the standard path the hook
records `Docker Desktop not found` in the log; surface that to the
operator instead of silently failing.

## Logs

All preflight output lands under `.cursor/hooks/logs/` (gitignored via
the project-wide `*.log` rule):

- `preflight.log` — main hook trace
- `sonar-up.log` — helper script trace + `npm run sonar:up` output
- `dev-server.log` — Vite stdout/stderr

When a gate-time issue shows up (sonar unreachable, preview blank),
tail those logs before re-running the preflight manually.
